1. 	Create container and go inside in one command:		-->		docker run -d --name [containername] -p [hostport]:[containerport] -it [imagename] /bin/bash
   	Example: docker run -d --name mycont -p 90:80 -it mycontimage /bin/bash

2. 	Create .tar file:		--> 	docker export container_id > filename.tar
					OR	docker export container_id -o filename.tar
								|
						 	Will create as snapshot
   
